# Keep the build context tiny and the image clean.
#
# 🔴 THIS FILE ONCE EXCLUDED package.json AND package-lock.json.
#
#    It was written when there was only a static web image, which does not need
#    them. Then the API arrived, and its Dockerfile begins:
#
#        COPY package.json package-lock.json ./
#        RUN npm ci
#
#    ...against a build context from which .dockerignore had silently removed both.
#    The build failed with:
#
#        failed to compute cache key: "/package-lock.json": not found
#
#    A file that exists on disk, in the same directory as the Dockerfile, that
#    Docker insists is not there. The error tells you nothing about why.
#
#    build.js now cross-checks every COPY in every Dockerfile against this file.
#    An ignore rule that hides a file the build needs will not build.

node_modules/

.git/
.gitignore
.dockerignore

# Docs and orchestration are not part of any image.
*.md
docker-compose.yml
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.api
playwright.config.js
e2e.spec.js

# Playwright output
test-results/
playwright-report/

# 🔴 NEVER BAKE A SECRET INTO AN IMAGE.
#    An image is a tarball. It gets pushed, pulled, cached and shared. A key
#    baked into a layer is a key you cannot rotate and cannot recall.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.p12

# Scratch
*.tmp
*.tmp.js
*.bak
